Constructor
-method used to initialize objects
-called when object is created
-initialize instance variables of object and perform operation
-do NOT have return type
-used to set initial values to an object when object is created

Default Constructors
-Java automatically provides default if a class doesn't define any constructor
-parameterless (takes no argument)
-initialize object's instance variable to default value

ex) class Constructor{
        int x;
        Constructor(int intputParam){
            //x = 42 with empty parameter//
             x = inputParam;}
            }

How to Call
class Creator{
    public static void main(String []args){
        Constructor objectOne = new Constructor();
        System.out.println(objectOne.x);
        } }
        //or//
        Constructor objectTwo = new Constructor(10);
        System.out.println(objectTwo.x);



